results.name: Let S be the sequence of power towers built of 2 and 3 sorted by their height and for equal heights - in lexicographic order: 2, 3, 2^2, 2^3, 3^2, 3^3, 2^2^2, 2^2^3 etc. A(n) = the permutation of indexes which reorders S by magnitude.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..14335
